15/02/2004
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- The municipalities of Gjilan, Kamenice and Artane are doing an excellent job at contributing to peace and stability in the province, said Lieutenant Colonel Allen Ponsini, commander of the US base in Gjilan, Camp Monteith. Speaking Friday (13 February) he praised the efforts of these communities to maintain multiethnicity in the province. "The people of those municipalities, just as in other municipalities, continue to show their will to forget the past and to be committed to their common future," said Ponsini. He added that the Kosovo Protection Corps has started to evolve into a civilian structure, geared to handle natural disasters. (BBC - 13/02/04)
